vsParam:
Oh, so this place is called the Bressisle, huh.
It's entirely different from my world.

Ah, my name is Wilbell!
I'm new to this strange place... Nice to meet you!

Sure, nice to meet you, too! I mean,
you are dressed like a witch from a storybook!

No! I-I'm not. What are you talking about?
I couldn't... understand...

D-don't talk nonsense! No witch would be
bold enough to dress as a witch.

Hmm, it's pretty common, no?
Marjoram Sensei dresses like that.

Ah. You are a witch, Wilbell.
Why didn't you say that earlier?

Boo-hoo, I didn't expect to get exposed so quickly...
Aren't you shocked!?

Hmm... I wanted to ask you why we should be shocked.
I'm a student of wizardology.

... Uh, wizardology?
So, witches and wizards are common in this world, huh?

B-bravo!
I thought I'd get scolded by grandmother again...
Wilbell, were you trying to conceal your identity as a witch?

Yes. In my world,
witches and wizards must hide their identities.

There's great power in magic, so we try to keep it from falling
into the wrong hands by hiding our identities.

But magic is quite common here... Does it mean that
I can use magic whenever I want?

Ha ha, so excited, huh?...
Are you so eager to use magic, Wilbell?

Of course! My magic skills should be further honed,
but I aspire to become a great witch someday!

Ah, Wilbell, why don't stay at the Academy?
It has a Wizardology Department!

That's right. Joining the Wizardology Department
will greatly help with your skill honing.

Er... hmm, that sounds wonderful.
Then I'll stay if you all want me to.

Nice!
Glad to have you around, Wilbell!
